+\emph{Status (v1.4): resolved in the soft branch; hard branch forward-pointed.}
+The closed form of the WKB amplitude $\alpha(b)$ at the four equianharmonic
+$j(\mathrm{Jac}(C_b))=0$ cubic families
 ($(\alpha_3,\alpha_2,\alpha_1,\alpha_0) = (1,-3,3,a_0)$ with
-$a_0\in\{-3,1,2,3\}$). The H6 prediction (proposed during the v1.3
-absorption cycle) asserts $A_{\mathrm{true}}-6 = 0$ exactly at the
-equianharmonic cell, with the leading transcendental amplitude
-governed by the Chowla--Selberg
-$\Gamma(1/3)$ formula~\cite{ChowlaSelberg1967,Yu99} at the
-imaginary-quadratic discriminant $D=-3$. Session~T2 Phase~D
-(\texttt{phase\_d\_pslq.py}, $\mathrm{dps}=4000$, $N_{\max}=480$)
-triggered a literal $5\sigma$-scale halt on $A_{\mathrm{fit}}-6$
-across the four families, but the ${\ge}50\!\times$ N-scaling
-shrinkage from R1.1 ($N\!\le\!67$) to T2-D ($N\!\le\!480$)
-identifies this as a finite-$N$ tail-window artefact of the
-four-parameter WKB ansatz (Remark~\ref{rem:j-zero-finite-N}). PSLQ
-closure was deferred because amplitude extraction by lstsq capped
-at $\sim\!14$ digits is insufficient to detect a $\Gamma(1/3)$-basis
-relation against the B19 augmented basis (Session~T2,
-claim~T2-D6). The recommended protocol (relay tag~\textsc{T2.5d}) is
-a redesigned five-parameter WKB ansatz $y_N = -A\,N\log N + \alpha\,N
-- \beta\log N + \gamma + c_1/N$ at $\mathrm{dps}\ge 8000$,
-$N_{\max}\ge 1200$, with $\alpha$ extracted directly to
-${\ge}40$ digits before PSLQ.
+$a_0\in\{-3,1,2,3\}$) was the principal forward-pointed open problem at
+v1.3. Session~T2 Phase~D (\texttt{phase\_d\_pslq.py}, $\mathrm{dps}=4000$,
+$N_{\max}=480$) had triggered a literal $5\sigma$-scale halt on
+$A_{\mathrm{fit}}-6$ across the four families, identified at v1.3 as a
+finite-$N$ tail-window artefact of the four-parameter WKB ansatz
+(Remark~\ref{rem:j-zero-finite-N}). The v1.3 recommended protocol
+(relay tag~\textsc{T2.5d}) called for a redesigned five-parameter WKB ansatz
+$y_N = -A\,N\log N + \alpha\,N - \beta\log N + \gamma + c_1/N$ at
+$\mathrm{dps}\ge 8000$, $N_{\max}\ge 1200$, with $\alpha$ extracted directly
+to ${\ge}40$ digits before PSLQ.
+
+\paragraph{v1.4 closure (soft branch).}
+The T2.5d protocol was executed as Prompt~014 (T25D-RETRY-13PARAM, SIARC
+bridge SHA \texttt{e857172}, 2026-05-02) at the strengthened parameter
+window $\mathrm{dps}=25000$ / $N \le 1200$ and at an 11-parameter
+square-exact LIN refit at $K_{\mathrm{FIT}}=7$ (Judgment call \#1 of the
+Prompt 014 handoff).  The result is the verdict
+\textsf{PASS\_A\_EQ\_6\_ONLY}: across the four $j=0$ cubic families
+(Q\_30, Q\_31, Q\_32, Q\_33) the WKB leading exponent $A_{\mathrm{lin}}$
+satisfies
+\[
+   \max_{30 \le i \le 33}\, |A_{\mathrm{lin}}^{(i)} - 6|
+   \;\le\; 3.09\times 10^{-23},
+\]
+clearing the $10^{-15}$ minimum target with $8+$ orders of margin.
+PSLQ on the 17-member deduplicated H6 Chowla--Selberg basis B19+
+(maxcoeff $=10^{50}$, tolerance $=10^{-40}$) returned \emph{no}
+non-trivial $\Gamma(1/3)$ relation in any of the four families.
+We read this as: $A=6$ to PSLQ-detection precision, with no detected
+Chowla--Selberg amplitude correction in the H6 basis at the present
+precision.
+
+\paragraph{Q23 PSLQ basis hygiene.}
+The closure runs in the \emph{deduplicated} 17-member basis (NOT the
+literal 18-basis). The literal 18-basis contains the
+$\mathbb{Q}$-redundant pair
+$\{\sqrt{3},\,\Gamma(1/3)\Gamma(2/3)/(2\pi)\}$ via the
+$\Gamma$-reflection identity; running PSLQ on the literal basis
+returns the trivial relation
+$1\cdot\sqrt{3} - 3\cdot\mathrm{CS}_{\sqrt{3}} = 0$
+with target coefficient $=0$, i.e.\ no Chowla--Selberg signal. Q23
+PSLQ basis-hygiene rule (deduplicate before running PSLQ) is recorded
+in the Prompt 014 \texttt{unexpected\_finds.json}.
+
+\paragraph{Soft / hard branch split.}
+Closure is recorded in the \emph{soft branch} (algebraic-combinatorial
+amplitude refit on saved $\mathrm{cf\_value}$ series, no new high-dps
+$\mathtt{mpmath}$ generation needed). The hard-branch stretch goal
+$|\delta| < 10^{-30}$ is \emph{not} achieved at v1.4 and remains
+forward-pointed not-blocking; it would require $K_{\mathrm{FIT}}=9$
+on extended series at $N\le 2400$ / $\mathrm{dps}\ge 44{,}300$ along
+the Q22 path-(b) numerical-escalation ladder. The annotation
+\emph{(SOFT-BRANCH; HARD-BRANCH-PENDING)} is recorded with the closure
+to prevent silent inheritance of an unqualified closure state in
+downstream documents. Picture-chain v1.20+ tag form is
+\textsf{M7\_V0\_CLOSED (SOFT-BRANCH; HARD-BRANCH-PENDING)}.
+
